item.description:
WebSocket endpoint at ws://localhost:8080/ws

This is a reference request -- WebSocket connections cannot be made directly from Postman REST requests. Use the Postman WebSocket tab or a WebSocket client.

Message protocol:

1. Authenticate:
{"type": "auth", "payload": {"token": "<access_token>"}}

Response: {"type": "authenticated", "user": "<username>"}

2. Subscribe to markets:
{"type": "subscribe", "payload": {"market_ids": ["mkt_cricket_001", "mkt_football_002"]}}

Response (streaming): {"type": "odds_update", "payload": {"market_id": "...", "runners": [...], "timestamp": "..."}}

3. Ping/Pong:
{"type": "ping"}
Response: {"type": "pong"}
